observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
 Create an Inventory Team to conduct the yearly physical inventory of PPE, in compliance with Section 57, Volume II of the Local Government Accounting , with the result thereof reported in proper format and substance, to check the accountability ofproperty custodianship;
 Reconcile the inventory report with the accounting and property records for proper adjustment of the deficiencies if any to reflect the accurate balances of the PPE accounts. To facilitate reconciliation, the accountant must maintain the PPELC as provided in Paragraphs b and d of Appendix 8, Volume II of the LGAS;
 Comply with PPSAS 17 by revising the Notes to Financial Statements to fully disclose the required financial data onPPE.

